ZH: 我们明天要坐火车去上海。
EN: We are taking the train to Shanghai tomorrow.

ZH: 请问这个火车是去北京的吗？
EN: Excuse me, is this train going to Beijing?

ZH: 火车站附近有地铁站吗？
EN: Is there a subway station near the train station?

ZH: 坐火车比坐飞机便宜吗？
EN: Is taking the train cheaper than taking a plane?

ZH: 我们赶快去赶火车吧！
EN: Let's hurry up to catch the train!

ZH: 我坐过很多次高铁了。
EN: I have taken the high-speed train many times.

ZH: 火车已经晚点一个小时了。
EN: The train is already one hour late.

ZH: 坐火车可以欣赏窗外的美景。
EN: You can enjoy the scenery outside the window when taking the train.

ZH: 我爸爸是一名火车司机。
EN: My dad is a train driver.

ZH: 我们可以在火车上买饮料和小吃。
EN: We can buy drinks and snacks on the train.

ZH: 马上就要下火车了，请大家准备好行李。
EN: We will be getting off the train shortly, please prepare your luggage.

ZH: 这趟火车的票已经全都卖光了。
EN: All tickets for this train have been sold out.

ZH: 坐火车要注意车厢里的温度。
EN: Pay attention to the temperature inside the train.

ZH: 高铁比普通列车更快更舒适。
EN: High-speed trains are faster and more comfortable than regular trains.

ZH: 火车上有免费的无线上网。
EN: There is free wifi on the train.

ZH: 我给你推荐一家特色的火车餐厅。
EN: I recommend you a special train restaurant.

ZH: 火车站离我家很近，步行只需五分钟。
EN: The train station is very close to my house, only a five-minute walk.

ZH: 妈妈常常坐火车去拜访她的好朋友。
EN: Mom often takes the train to visit her good friend.

ZH: 火车开得很平稳，不容易晕车。
EN: The train runs very smoothly, making it less likely to get motion sickness.

ZH: 火车是我最喜欢的交通工具之一。
EN: The train is one of my favorite means of transportation.
